Find the greatest common divisor of $2863$ and $1344$.
inference:
Using the Euclidean Algorithm:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Divide 2863 by 1344:
    $2863 = 2 \times 1344 + 175$
    \item Divide 1344 by 175:
    $1344 = 7 \times 175 + 119$
    \item Divide 175 by 119:
    $175 = 1 \times 119 + 56$
    \item Divide 119 by 56:
    $119 = 2 \times 56 + 5$
    \item Divide 56 by 5:
    $56 = 11 \times 5 + 1$
    \item Divide 5 by 1:
    $5 = 5 \times 1 + 0$
\end{enumerate}
The last non-zero remainder is 1.
Therefore, the greatest common divisor of 2863 and 1344 is 1.

Final Answer: $\boxed{1}$. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
We use the Euclidean algorithm.  \begin{align*}
\text{gcd}\,(2863,1344)&=\text{gcd}\,(2863-1344 \cdot 2 ,1344) \\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175,1344)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175,1344-175 \cdot 7)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175,119)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175-119,119)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(56,119)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(56,119-56 \cdot 2)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(56,7).
\end{align*}Since $56$ is a multiple of $7$, the greatest common divisor is $\boxed{7}$.
